description.p:
Specifically, the present invention takes the following constitutions.
[1] A composition for controlling plant diseases comprising, as active ingredients, a compound represented by formula (1):
wherein X1 represents a methyl group; X2 represents a methylamino group; and X3 represents a 2,5-dimethylphenyl group;
and at least one azole compound selected from the group consisting of bromuconazole, cyproconazole, difenoconazole, fenbuconazole, fluquinconazole, hexaconazole, imibenconazole, ipconazole, myclobutanil, prothioconazole, simeconazole, tetraconazole, triticonazole and metconazole which has a weight ratio of the compound represented by formula (1) to the at least one azole compound falling within the range of from 0.0125:1 to 500:1;
[2] The composition according to [1], wherein the azole compound is at least one azole compound selected from the group consisting of bromuconazole, difenoconazole, fluquinconazole, ipconazole, prothioconazole, tetraconazole, triticonazole and metconazole;
[3] A plant seed treated with effective amounts of the compound represented by formula (1) of [1] and at least one azole compound selected from the group consisting of bromuconazole, cyproconazole, difenoconazole, fenbuconazole, fluquinconazole, hexaconazole, imibenconazole, ipconazole, myclobutanil, prothioconazole, simeconazole, tetraconazole, triticonazole and metconazole in a weight ratio as defined in [1];
[4] A method for controlling plant diseases which comprises applying, to a plant or a locus where a plant is allowed to grow, effective amounts of the compound represented by formula (1) of [1] and at least one azole compound selected from the group consisting of bromuconazole, cyproconazole, difenoconazole, fenbuconazole, fluquinconazole, hexaconazole, imibenconazole, ipconazole, myclobutanil, prothioconazole, simeconazole, tetraconazole, triticonazole and metconazole in a weight ratio as defined in [1]; and
[5] Combined use for controlling plant diseases of the compound represented by formula (1) of [1] and at least one azole compound selected from the group consisting of bromuconazole, cyproconazole, difenoconazole, fenbuconazole, fluquinconazole, hexaconazole, imibenconazole, ipconazole, myclobutanil, prothioconazole, simeconazole, tetraconazole, triticonazole and metconazole in a weight ratio as defined in [1].

claim.claim-text:
A composition for controlling plant diseases comprising, as active ingredients, a compound represented by formula (1):

wherein X1 is a methyl group, X2 is a methylamino group, and X3 is a 2,5-dimethylphenyl group;

and at least one azole compound selected from the group consisting of bromuconazole, cyproconazole, difenoconazole, fenbuconazole, fluquinconazole, hexaconazole, imibenconazole, ipconazole, myclobutanil,, prothioconazole, simeconazole, tetraconazole, triticonazole and metconazole;

which has a weight ratio of the compound represented by formula (1) to the at least one azole compound falling within the range of from 0.0125:1 to 500:1.

Composition pour contrôler des maladies des plantes comprenant, comme ingrédients actifs, un composé représenté par la formule (1) :

dans laquelle X1 est un groupe méthyle, X2 est un groupe méthylamino et X3 est un groupe 2,5-diméthylphényle ;

et au moins un composé d'azole choisi dans le groupe constitué de bromuconazole, cyproconazole, difénoconazole, fenbuconazole, fluquinconazole, hexaconazole, imibenconazole, ipconazole, myclobutanil, prothioconazole, siméconazole, tétraconazole, triticonazole et metconazole ;

qui a un rapport en poids du composé représenté par la formule (1) sur l'au moins un composé d'azole situé dans la plage de 0,0125:1 à 500:1.
